-- Wylfa-3 Nuclear Reactor in U.K. Halted Since Aug. 26, Data Shows
-- B y   G r a n t   S m i t h
-- 2012-08-28T06:51:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-28/wylfa-3-nuclear-reactor-in-u-k-halted-since-aug-26-data-shows.html
Unit 3 at the Wyfla nuclear power
plant in Anglesey,  Wales , halted at about 10:25 a.m. on Aug. 26
London time,  National Grid Plc (NG/)  data show.  Unit 2 at the plant, which had halted on Aug. 9, restarted
at about 7:20 p.m. on Aug. 25, according to the data. The
Nuclear Decommissioning Authority owns the site and it is
operated by Magnox North Ltd.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Grant Smith in London at 
 gsmith52@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Lars Paulsson at 
